<UML:Comment id="8a72b76b-26fa-11f1-9461-e1dc6fffddd4">
<body>
<val>Moves of BallMover, should not be saved in a variable for input and cpu mover, it should be Ball Mover duty to guarantee a getMove is always correct when done, and also BallMover should update the movement in case of necessity

getMove should return Null to inertial 
Movement</val>
</body>
<presentation>
<reflist>
<ref refid="8a72bbf5-26fa-11f1-9bad-e1dc6fffddd4"/>
</reflist>
</presentation>
</UML:Comment>
<UML:CommentItem id="8a72bbf5-26fa-11f1-9bad-e1dc6fffddd4">
<matrix>
<val>(1.0, 0.0, 0.0, 1.0, 313.36782073974615, 681.3861083984374)</val>
</matrix>
<top-left>
<val>(-194.07290954589843, 0.0)</val>
</top-left>
<width>
<val>294.0729095458984</val>
</width>
<height>
<val>178.0</val>
</height>
<diagram>
<ref refid="f6b56593-26ef-11f1-a495-e1dc6fffddd4"/>
</diagram>
<subject>
<ref refid="8a72b76b-26fa-11f1-9461-e1dc6fffddd4"/>
</subject>
</UML:CommentItem>
<UML:Comment id="12b61125-26fb-11f1-91c2-e1dc6fffddd4">
<body>
<val>Assign an objet to a variable in java is atomical. 

CollisionResolver can't start before the BallMover.getMove() on every balls: Ball hit wall, collider give ball new speed, update move was already applied, get move give movent toward the wall, the ball go outside the map.

CollisionResolver can't start before every ball completely did ball.updatePosition() -&gt; problem with lost update: ball should stop, but it goes against an object. Collision resolver read a speed, then updatePosition set speed to 0. After collision resolver resolve collision and set the speed to the old value in a different direction.

without friction there is the same problem: Ball ha a certain direction that is readed by both update and collision collision change direction but in the end update put the old direction</val>
</body>
<presentation>
<reflist>
<ref refid="12b61592-26fb-11f1-a0fd-e1dc6fffddd4"/>
</reflist>
</presentation>
</UML:Comment>
